ly</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> angels) or whatever else they can use to seem deep. Sure these overtones can be great plot-wise at times, but some people have found them to be just plain confusing and that they tend to fly right over your head if you're not really connected to a religion... And other times, some references just seem kinda pointless (can ANYONE justify that angel reference in Metropolis? Or the mentioning of the Book of Revelations in Big O?). <br><br>Anyway, I talk too much..... what do you think; <br>religious overtones -- good or bad? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uironjackal64.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ironjackal64</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=ff00ff>S</font><font color=ff00cc>&</font><font color=ff0099>M</font> <font color=ff0066>Q</font><font color=ff0033>u</font><font color=ff0000>e</font><font color=ff3300>e</font><font color=ff6600>n</font></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/20/02 9:59:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1955.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://liquid2k.com/oolong/insanesquirrel.gif height=186 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are religious overtones a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> i don't think religious references are a bad thing. I mean, look at a lot of american movies and stuff are starting to have people who do yoga and meditate and stuff like that... it's kinda the same way with references to christianity in anime. They're not always very fitting, but it's used cuz christianity is starting to become bigger in japan and there's a demographic for it. I don't really find them too confusing, sometimes if there's something i really think i need to get i look it up on the internet. I'm non christian, and it doesn't offend me, and i don't really think it should offend most christian otaku unless they're like really conservative. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugenchi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Genchi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/21/02 7:28:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1955.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://genchi.digitalrice.com/ABe/ABchicksitting.jpg height=158 width=104></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are religious overtones a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> Oolong stole my post before I posted it!<br><br><br>Oolong is the devil!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uprismrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PrismRX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/21/02 9:19:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1955.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are religious overtones a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> Nothing's wrong with it, religions in a necesary part of some storylines and things.  As Oolong said. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=terminalspiritdisease>Terminal Spirit Disease</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/21/02 7:07:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1955.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   !</span><hr size=1> I hate to dick with semantics here, but since you said <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> over</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->tones, I might be inclined to dislike such a piece. There are some pretty cool movies and books with religious overtones--Kevin Smith's &quot;Dogma&quot; being my favorite--but what makes those so entertaining is that they meddle in a little comical blasphemy, they're not so over didactic, and they're not the same old boring stories and parables. <br><br>I've yet to see an anime handle overtones well, but Spriggan used some pretty good religion inspired plot elements well (you know, the whole Noah's Ark thing). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubluntman182.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bluntman182</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/29/02 4:43:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1955.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Are religious overtones a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> I think it gives people the wrong impression about christians and christianity.  In all the anime I've seen not one of the characters would be considered christian.  O well what can ya do? *shrug* <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right 